Package civitas.celestis.math.matrix

Class LongMatrix

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.math.matrix.LongMatrix
All Implemented Interfaces:
RawLongMatrix<LongMatrix>, Collectable<Long>, Grid<Long>, Group<Long>, Mappable<Grid.Index,Long>, Transformable<Long>, Serializable, Iterable<Long>
public class LongMatrix extends Object implements RawLongMatrix<LongMatrix>
A numerical grid structure of raw primitive longs.

This class is preferred over grids of boxed Long due to less overhead in dealing with objects.

Since longs are an efficient container of 64 bits of data, this matrix can be used to house any form of data which can be packed into 64 bits.

      @Nonnull public LongMatrix merge(@Nonnull Grid<Long> g, @Nonnull BiFunction<? super Long,? super Long,Long> f) throws IllegalArgumentException
      Merges this grid with another grid of the same dimensions. The merger function f is applied to each component, and the resulting grid is returned.

      For example, if a sum function (x, y) -> x + y was provided, this would return the sum of the two grids of numbers.
